    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.34,
      "end": 23.7,
      "text": "ASAP's Fables",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 25.38,
      "end": 27.72,
      "text": "The old woman and the doctor.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 29.88,
      "end": 33.9,
      "text": "An old woman became almost totally blind from a disease of the eyes,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 34.58,
      "end": 39.02,
      "text": "and after consulting a doctor made an agreement with him in the presence of witnesses",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 39.02,
      "end": 42.66,
      "text": "that she should pay him a high fee if he cured her,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 43.22,
      "end": 45.26,
      "text": "while if he failed he was to receive nothing.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 46.52,
      "end": 49.3,
      "text": "The doctor accordingly prescribed a course of treatment,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 49.96,
      "end": 54.46,
      "text": "and every time he paid her a visit, he took away with him some article out of the house,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 54.46,
      "end": 58.28,
      "text": "until at last when he visited her for the last time,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 58.78,
      "end": 61.16,
      "text": "and the cure was complete, there was nothing left.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 62.36,
      "end": 66.44,
      "text": "When the old woman saw that the house was empty, she refused to pay him his fee,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 67.02,
      "end": 72.5,
      "text": "and after repeated refusals on her part, he sued her before the magistrates for payment of her debt.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 73.48,
      "end": 76.48,
      "text": "On being brought into court, she was ready with her defense.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 78.06,
      "end": 83.52,
      "text": "The claimant, said she, has stated the facts about our agreement correctly.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 84.64,
      "end": 89.48,
      "text": "I undertook to pay him a fee if he cured me, and he on his part,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-020",
      "start": 89.96,
      "end": 92.14,
      "text": "promised to charge nothing if he failed.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-021",
      "start": 93.16,
      "end": 100.36,
      "text": "Now he says I am cured, but I say that I am blinder than ever, and I can prove what I say.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-022",
      "start": 101.28,
      "end": 105.98,
      "text": "When my eyes were bad, I could at any rate see well enough to be aware",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-023",
      "start": 105.98,
      "end": 110.12,
      "text": "that my house contained a certain amount of furniture and other things,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-024",
      "start": 111.04,
      "end": 117.14,
      "text": "but now, when according to him I am cured, I am entirely unable to see anything there at all.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-025",
      "start": 119.72,
      "end": 122.0,
      "text": "End of the old woman and the doctor.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
